data.description: Back on market due to financing difficulties.  All requested repairs completed. Refreshed, revitalized and move-in ready.  The executor for the estate wanted to sell the home that her mother would have been proud to pass onto another owner. The roof was replaced.  The foundation was leveled. Wood grain flooring was installed that compliments the kitchen tile.  Plumbing tunnel inspection was completed. .  As a result, plumbing was replaced.  Warranties are in place for the roof, foundation and plumbing work.  Fresh  paint can be seen.   The executor didn't stop there, bathrooms were updated, the kitchen got an updated counter-top, sink and faucet.  A shiny stainless-steel dishwasher has been installed along with disposal and vent hood.  Recently added fans can be seen in the bedrooms and eating area.  The laundry room was given a face-lift. TLC to the front stone patio with some new stone and seal, give the house a really nice curbside appeal.  This home is truly a golden oldie, refreshed, revitalized and waiting for a new owner.   See Outstanding Feature sheet in Associated Documents.  Previous inspection and list of repairs in Associated Documents
